Heat the oil in a saucepan over a medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and fry for 2-3 minutes, or until soft.Add the potato and saut&eactute;e for two minutes.Add the stock, bring to the boil, then simmer for eight minutes.Add the spinach and cook for a further two minutes.Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper and add the chervil.Transfer to a food processor and blend until smooth.To serve, pour the soup into a serving bowl and pour the cream in a swirl over the soup.